  <brief_title>The Effect of Licorice Root Extract and Pomegranate Juice on Atherosclerotic Parameters in Diabetic Patients</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>HaEmek Medical Center, Israel</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>HaEmek Medical Center, Israel</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study will check whether taking 100 mg of licorice root extract or 250 cc of pomegranate
      juice daily by men with diabetes mellitus who are non-smokers and already treated with
      statins decreases the risk of developing atherosclerosis. The hypothesis of the study is that
      natural anti-oxidants (such as licorice root extract and pomegranate juice), by scavenging
      free radicals, retard and may even reverse atherosclerosis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
